body:
Not really a bug, but it makes parametric circuit generation almost impossible.
The following code initialises an array of ~5k integer elements in a function evaluated in constant context (the mylist local parameter would eventually be used in a generate block to create a custom circuit during elaboration, with a more complicated algorithm, of course).
On my laptop even just linting it ("verilator --lint-only mytest.sv") uses nearly **6GB in memory**, let alone the 64bit case.
```
module mytest #(parameter NBITS = 32) ();
   localparam NUMCIRCUITS = 5*NBITS*NBITS;
   typedef integer unsigned list_t[NUMCIRCUITS];

   function list_t make_list;
      for (int j=0; j<NUMCIRCUITS; ++j) make_list[j] = j;
   endfunction

   localparam list_t mylist = make_list();
   initial
     $display($size(mylist), mylist[0], mylist[NUMCIRCUITS-1]);
endmodule
```
```
builds/mytest/simulator +verilator+rand+reset+2
       5120         0      5119
```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?

